{title: Family Tree}
{artist: Keith Whitley}
{composer: Written by F. Dycus and Max Barnes}

[C]Papa lays [F]in a county [C]rest home
Mama lives [G7]on a rich man’s [C]farm
Sister moved in [F]with a [C]stranger
And here I lay [G7]in another's [C]arms

And the [F]leaves are slowly [C]falling
Falling [F]from the family [C]tree
Yes the [F]leaves are slowly [C]falling
And the last one [G7]to fall is [C]me

Should have known the [F]winds of [C]autumn
Finally blow [G7]our worlds a[C]part
Here I lay [F]with another [C]woman
There you reign with [G7]a broken [C]heart

Yes the [F]leaves are slowly [C]falling
Falling [F]from the family [C]tree
Yes the [F]leaves are slowly [C]falling
And the last one [G7]to fall is [C]me
Repeat last verse